name: AG TJ Donovan
tweet: Tonight we heard from President Joe Biden a vision for America that helps everyone and leaves no one behind.   As he said it is a unity agenda that we must get it done. We can tackle the opioid crisis, prescription drug prices, address mental health, and support our veterans.

tweet: I am deeply concerned about the actions being taken in Texas against LGBTQ+ youth.   I have stood firmly in support of LGBTQ+ rights and will continue to do all that I can to ensure those rights are protected.

name: AG TJ Donovan
tweet: Justice Breyer has a legacy of protecting voting rights, healthcare, and our environment. I want to thank him for his service and dedication.  Soon, I look forward to @JoeBiden nominating a Justice that will continue that legacy and more.

name: AG TJ Donovan
tweet: On this anniversary of Roe v. Wade I am thinking of the grave threat banning abortion poses to our communities & families.   Banning abortion is both wrong and unsafe. I am committed to fighting to protect reproductive rights & access to abortion. We will not back down.

tweet: Justice Sotomayor writes: “The court should have put and end to this madness months ago, before S.B. 8 first went into effect.”  I could not agree more with Justice Sotomayor. Abortion is healthcare and healthcare is a right.
